Now I'd like to do a painting...

755
01:24:58,630 --> 01:25:03,533
but all I have are lines... a face.

756
01:25:06,004 --> 01:25:08,029
Posthumous portraiture?

757
01:25:09,842 --> 01:25:11,571
I'm not joking.

758
01:25:12,778 --> 01:25:15,269
No, of course you're not.
I'm sorry.

759
01:25:15,347 --> 01:25:17,577
You've set me quite a task.

760
01:25:20,552 --> 01:25:24,784
He was a quiet man. The thing I most
remember him for were his silences.

761
01:25:24,857 --> 01:25:26,290
It was...

762
01:25:28,760 --> 01:25:31,695
as if he were always listening
to something inside...

763
01:25:33,065 --> 01:25:34,498
some voice.

764
01:25:36,034 --> 01:25:40,596
He never talked about it,
so I never knew what it was.

765
01:25:40,672 --> 01:25:42,606
He was a good man...

766
01:25:47,045 --> 01:25:49,809
but he lived as if
he were a stranger here.

767
01:25:49,882 --> 01:25:51,816
He never let anything touch him.

768
01:25:51,884 --> 01:25:54,944
He became absorbed in things,
his job mostly.

769
01:25:56,321 --> 01:25:58,255
He worked hard.

770
01:25:59,224 --> 01:26:01,158
He became more detached and...

771
01:26:02,861 --> 01:26:06,319
Always a look around his eyes
as if he were...

772
01:26:06,398 --> 01:26:08,332
trying to say something.

773
01:26:11,003 --> 01:26:12,766
I don't know what.

774
01:26:14,273 --> 01:26:17,401
Protest against what
he'd surrendered his life to?

775
01:26:21,647 --> 01:26:23,581
I never knew what he wanted...

776
01:26:26,585 --> 01:26:28,519
and I don't think he ever knew.

777
01:26:31,290 --> 01:26:34,726
He fought so hard
for what he'd been taught to want...

778
01:26:34,793 --> 01:26:37,591
and when he got it,
he just grew more and more confused.

779
01:26:37,663 --> 01:26:39,597
The silences grew longer.

780
01:26:43,068 --> 01:26:45,002
We never talked about it.

781
01:26:47,406 --> 01:26:49,340
We lived our lives
in a polite...

782
01:26:51,310 --> 01:26:52,743
celibate truce.

783
01:26:54,646 --> 01:26:57,672
Arthur had been dead
a long, long time...

784
01:26:57,749 --> 01:27:00,183
before they found him
in that hotel room.

785
01:27:05,857 --> 01:27:10,157
Well, I guess I can't tell you
much more. Enough?

786
01:27:13,665 --> 01:27:15,098
Yes, it is.

787
01:27:20,305 --> 01:27:22,330
I really should be going.

788
01:27:24,543 --> 01:27:28,570
I hope I've been some help.

789
01:27:36,555 --> 01:27:37,988
Yes, you have.

790
01:27:41,059 --> 01:27:42,492
Very much.

791
01:28:05,917 --> 01:28:08,681
<i>You said that you wanted a memento.</i>

792
01:28:10,088 --> 01:28:13,649
<i>It won't be a painting, I'm afraid,</i>
<i>but it's all I have.</i>

793
01:28:27,606 --> 01:28:29,972
I'm sorry, Mr. Wilson.

794
01:28:30,042 --> 01:28:31,634
It doesn't matter.

795
01:28:44,890 --> 01:28:47,552
- I want to go back.
- Of course, sir.

796
01:28:48,860 --> 01:28:50,987
No, I don't mean to California.

797
01:28:52,564 --> 01:28:54,156
To the company.

798
01:28:55,233 --> 01:28:57,167
Start again, all over.

799
01:28:59,905 --> 01:29:02,999
Antiochus Wilson can die,
can't he?

800
01:29:05,944 --> 01:29:07,377
The company.

801
01:29:08,547 --> 01:29:09,980
Is it possible?

802
01:29:12,351 --> 01:29:13,943
I think so, sir.

803
01:29:22,027 --> 01:29:23,460
Begin again.

804
01:29:26,788 --> 01:29:28,221
Quite honestly...

805
01:29:29,424 --> 01:29:31,790
I'm not the least bit sorry...

806
01:29:31,860 --> 01:29:34,886
because there were certain mistakes
made in my case...

807
01:29:34,963 --> 01:29:37,761
Of course, but before we go
into all that, let me ask you...

808
01:29:37,832 --> 01:29:42,166
whether you can recommend
and sponsor a new client.

809
01:29:45,373 --> 01:29:46,863
What?

810
01:29:46,941 --> 01:29:48,568
An acquaintance outside...

811
01:29:48,643 --> 01:29:51,612
whom you feel would benefit
by the company's services.

812
01:29:51,680 --> 01:29:53,671
You were sponsored
yourself, you know.

813
01:29:55,216 --> 01:29:57,480
Oh, yes, of course.

814
01:29:57,552 --> 01:29:59,782
A business associate, perhaps.
Someone down the street.

815
01:29:59,854 --> 01:30:02,448
You don't have to be intimately
acquainted with a man...

816
01:30:02,524 --> 01:30:05,789
to realize he'd be receptive
to the sort of opportunity we offer.

817
01:30:10,131 --> 01:30:13,498
I'm sorry. Right now,
I just can't seem to...

818
01:30:13,568 --> 01:30:17,163
What I mean is,
I'd like to think about it.

819
01:30:17,238 --> 01:30:18,830
That's all we ask.

820
01:30:18,907 --> 01:30:23,469
As you can imagine, our business
is acquired through present clients.

821
01:30:23,545 --> 01:30:26,173
It's a word-of-mouth operation.

822
01:30:26,247 --> 01:30:29,739
You don't suppose we can advertise
in magazines and newspapers.

823
01:30:31,286 --> 01:30:32,947
No, of course not.

824
01:30:34,389 --> 01:30:36,857
I think you'll come up
with something.

825
01:30:38,293 --> 01:30:40,056
Hold it. Thank you.

826
01:30:40,128 --> 01:30:41,755
Hold your arm up, please.

827
01:30:41,830 --> 01:30:44,162
- Excuse me. I don't understand.
- That's it.

828
01:30:44,232 --> 01:30:47,395
- Is all this really necessary?
- 131/2. Profile.

829
01:30:47,469 --> 01:30:50,870
- Turn sideways.
- Is this necessary for...

830
01:30:50,939 --> 01:30:52,497
Hold it.

831
01:30:52,574 --> 01:30:54,599
That's it. Back view.

832
01:30:54,676 --> 01:30:58,168
- What is this, preliminary for surgery?
- Certainly.

833
01:30:58,246 --> 01:31:01,044
Ayear's gone by. A lot happens
to the human body in a year.

834
01:31:07,989 --> 01:31:09,923
This one is yours, sir.

835
01:32:25,834 --> 01:32:27,267
Hello, Arthur.

836
01:32:31,439 --> 01:32:33,373
- I don't believe I know you.
- It's me, buddy.

837
01:32:45,420 --> 01:32:47,320
You're Charlie?

838
01:32:47,388 --> 01:32:49,185
Guess I am, old buddy.

839
01:32:51,826 --> 01:32:54,351
What are you doing here?

840
01:32:55,296 --> 01:32:57,264
Same as yourself. Waiting.

841
01:32:59,334 --> 01:33:00,767
What's the matter?

842
01:33:03,238 --> 01:33:05,035
Oh, nothing.

843
01:33:06,941 --> 01:33:11,571
It's just that it's hard
to recognize somebody...

844
01:33:13,915 --> 01:33:17,180
and not recognize them
at the same time.

845
01:33:18,219 --> 01:33:20,153
How long have you been here?

846
01:33:21,656 --> 01:33:23,647
A while.

847
01:33:26,895 --> 01:33:28,829
When you phoned me, you were here?

848
01:33:30,331 --> 01:33:31,730
Even the first time?

849
01:33:33,001 --> 01:33:34,434
But you sounded...

850
01:33:36,571 --> 01:33:39,005
like the whole thing
was something tremendous...

851
01:33:39,073 --> 01:33:42,736
this rebirth, everything...

852
01:33:42,810 --> 01:33:44,744
even when you hadn't
made a go of it!

853
01:33:51,953 --> 01:33:54,786
I thought you'd have
a better chance.

854
01:33:54,856 --> 01:33:58,417
Good God! How long does a man
have to wait to get into surgery?

855
01:33:58,493 --> 01:34:00,017
Not long, usually.

856
01:34:01,596 --> 01:34:05,828
I had to stay around and
telephone you, if necessary...

857
01:34:05,900 --> 01:34:09,301
through your first adjustment,
but now...

858
01:34:09,370 --> 01:34:14,433
That's what you meant
about our being tied together.

859
01:34:18,379 --> 01:34:20,313
I couldn't help it.

860
01:34:22,116 --> 01:34:26,382
I had to find out
where I went wrong.

861
01:34:31,059 --> 01:34:33,254
The years I've spent...

862
01:34:33,328 --> 01:34:37,890
trying to get all the things
I was told were important...

863
01:34:38,833 --> 01:34:40,892
that I was supposed to want!

864
01:34:41,970 --> 01:34:43,403
Things!

865
01:34:44,606 --> 01:34:47,302
Not people...

866
01:34:47,375 --> 01:34:49,343
or meaning.

867
01:34:49,410 --> 01:34:51,640
Just things.

868
01:34:53,715 --> 01:34:56,616
And California was the same.

869
01:34:56,684 --> 01:35:01,621
They made the same decisions
for me all over again...

870
01:35:01,689 --> 01:35:04,419
and they were
the same things, really.

871
01:35:10,098 --> 01:35:12,658
It's going to be
different from now on.

872
01:35:15,136 --> 01:35:17,161
A new face and a name.

873
01:35:19,140 --> 01:35:21,472
I'll do the rest.

874
01:35:21,542 --> 01:35:23,806
I know it's going to be different.

875
01:35:25,813 --> 01:35:27,747
I suppose you do too.

876
01:35:33,921 --> 01:35:35,513
Good morning, gentlemen.

877
01:35:36,524 --> 01:35:38,048
Mr. Carlson, please.

878
01:35:45,099 --> 01:35:47,966
Charlie. You?

879
01:35:52,807 --> 01:35:56,368
- Art, l...
- Mr. Carlson, please.

880
01:36:05,156 --> 01:36:07,750
I have the feeling you're
going to make it this time.

881
01:36:14,365 --> 01:36:16,629
I'm sorry to disappoint
the rest of you.

882
01:36:16,701 --> 01:36:18,134
Perhaps tomorrow.

883
01:36:27,145 --> 01:36:30,273
You don't seem to understand
our problem.

884
01:36:30,348 --> 01:36:33,681
- I understand it perfectly.
- But you're not cooperating.

885
01:36:33,751 --> 01:36:38,017
I've told you over and over again,
I cannot think of anyone.

886
01:36:38,089 --> 01:36:40,717
- I can't believe that.
- I've been shuffled around long enough.

887
01:36:40,791 --> 01:36:42,725
I think it's time
I had the opportunity...

888
01:36:42,793 --> 01:36:45,819
to start living
some kind of meaningful existence.

889
01:36:45,897 --> 01:36:50,834
If I did sponsor someone, wouldn't
that delay my trip to surgery...

890
01:36:50,902 --> 01:36:54,201
in the event that I were needed
from time to time, to, say, advise him?

891
01:36:54,272 --> 01:36:57,867
No, that's not likely,
not if the selection is a good one.

892
01:36:59,243 --> 01:37:02,838
I'm sorry. I don't seem to be able
to think of a single soul.

893
01:37:02,914 --> 01:37:05,849
- You mean you deliberately won't.
- Have it your way.

894
01:37:08,519 --> 01:37:10,146
Very well.

895
01:37:10,221 --> 01:37:13,782
That will be all.
You can go back to the day room.

896
01:37:23,901 --> 01:37:25,562
Processing, please.

897
01:37:25,636 --> 01:37:30,300
This is Ruby.
On Wilson, 722...

898
01:37:30,374 --> 01:37:33,104
I think we can go
to the next stage now.

899
01:37:52,296 --> 01:37:53,729
Hello, son.

900
01:37:59,837 --> 01:38:01,270
Oh, sir, l...

901
01:38:04,208 --> 01:38:08,611
You know, I sure hoped you'd make it,
find your dream come true.

902
01:38:09,447 --> 01:38:12,848
- What?
- I said I sure hoped you'd make it...

903
01:38:12,917 --> 01:38:14,851
find your dream come true.

904
01:38:19,190 --> 01:38:20,623
I guess...

905
01:38:22,927 --> 01:38:24,861
I guess I never had a dream.

906
01:38:24,929 --> 01:38:29,764
Maybe that's it.
That sure might have been it.

907
01:38:32,203 --> 01:38:34,137
If I did have one...

908
01:38:35,873 --> 01:38:40,572
it certainly wasn't
Antiochus Wilson.

909
01:38:45,783 --> 01:38:47,978
This time...

910
01:38:48,052 --> 01:38:51,112
I've got to be allowed, sir,
to make my own decision.

911
01:38:51,188 --> 01:38:52,621
You know, son...

912
01:38:52,690 --> 01:38:56,922
when I began this business,
I was a young man with an idea.

913
01:38:56,994 --> 01:39:00,293
I wasn't aiming to make a lot
of money, helping others...

914
01:39:00,364 --> 01:39:02,559
helping them to find
a little happiness.

915
01:39:02,633 --> 01:39:04,658
Heck, not just the rich.

916
01:39:04,735 --> 01:39:06,828
I thought eventually...

917
01:39:06,904 --> 01:39:10,465
I got tremendous comfort in
the thought that, in my small way...

918
01:39:10,541 --> 01:39:13,601
I was waging a battle
against human misery...

919
01:39:13,678 --> 01:39:15,612
and I was too.

920
01:39:15,680 --> 01:39:19,446
Except we do have
a high percentage of failures.

921
01:39:19,517 --> 01:39:22,213
I guess that's to be expected...

922
01:39:22,286 --> 01:39:24,481
but it hurts me.

923
01:39:24,555 --> 01:39:27,922
Some reborns make a go of it.

924
01:39:27,992 --> 01:39:32,019
We're always working to find ways
to improve the system.

925
01:39:32,096 --> 01:39:33,688
Yeah, we make mistakes.

926
01:39:33,764 --> 01:39:36,892
The fact is, when our clients
first started coming back here...

927
01:39:36,967 --> 01:39:40,198
I wanted to chuck the whole thing,
but I couldn't.

928
01:39:40,271 --> 01:39:42,432
The organization
was pretty big by then.

929
01:39:43,107 --> 01:39:44,540
Now...

930
01:39:44,608 --> 01:39:47,771
board of directors,
on a profit-sharing basis.

931
01:39:49,246 --> 01:39:50,941
All those people.

932
01:39:51,015 --> 01:39:55,714
You've no idea what a financial
responsibility it turned into.

933
01:39:55,786 --> 01:39:59,586
Heck, we make mistakes,
but we admit them...

934
01:39:59,657 --> 01:40:01,591
and go forward.

935
01:40:01,659 --> 01:40:03,627
I won't see it in my lifetime...

936
01:40:03,694 --> 01:40:07,323
but some of the younger execs
like Ruby may.

937
01:40:07,398 --> 01:40:09,923
You can call it
wishful thinking, son...

938
01:40:10,000 --> 01:40:12,867
but life is built on wishing.

939
01:40:12,937 --> 01:40:15,371
You've got to just keep
plugging away at them.

940
01:40:15,439 --> 01:40:18,306
You can't give up...

941
01:40:18,376 --> 01:40:23,006
and you can't let the mistakes
jeopardize the dream.

942
01:40:29,620 --> 01:40:32,088
Well, here's your transportation.

943
01:40:32,156 --> 01:40:34,090
- What?
- Surgery, sir.

944
01:40:34,158 --> 01:40:37,924
- But I've got to talk to you.
- We're on a tight schedule. Please.

945
01:40:37,995 --> 01:40:40,793
Why, I didn't expect so soon.

946
01:40:40,865 --> 01:40:44,028
It's efficiency.
You're lucky we got a match so quick.

947
01:40:44,101 --> 01:40:47,127
Hop aboard, son. Up there.

948
01:40:47,204 --> 01:40:48,796
The doctors are waiting.

949
01:40:52,476 --> 01:40:55,104
That's just so you won't fall off.

950
01:40:55,179 --> 01:40:58,580
But there's things we have
to talk about. I mean, my identity...

951
01:40:58,649 --> 01:41:00,913
We will later.

952
01:41:00,985 --> 01:41:04,352
Just relax, son.
Everything's going to be just fine.

953
01:41:04,422 --> 01:41:07,414
The thing about doing it on my own.

954
01:41:07,491 --> 01:41:10,187
You see, it's so important...
choice.

955
01:41:11,529 --> 01:41:14,054
You've got to change.
We have to talk about it.

956
01:41:14,131 --> 01:41:16,929
We will.
I'll look into it personally.

957
01:41:19,904 --> 01:41:22,839
Remember, son. We've got to keep
plugging away at the dream.

958
01:41:22,907 --> 01:41:25,967
The mistakes teach us how.
It wasn't wasted. Remember that.

959
01:41:32,383 --> 01:41:34,476
My name is Dr. Morris, sir.

960
01:41:34,552 --> 01:41:38,215
According to our records, you
were reared in the Protestant faith.

961
01:41:38,289 --> 01:41:41,486
Did you convert to any other
during your adjustment?

962
01:41:43,861 --> 01:41:45,294
Good, good!

963
01:41:45,362 --> 01:41:49,321
That is, good in the sense
that we have a certain definition.

964
01:41:49,400 --> 01:41:52,631
I am not suggesting
that being a Protestant...

965
01:41:52,703 --> 01:41:55,297
is any better
than being a Catholic or Jew.

966
01:41:55,372 --> 01:41:59,502
As a matter of fact, I am qualified
to care for you in those faiths as well.

967
01:41:59,577 --> 01:42:03,536
I was ordained in each...
a rabbi, priest and minister.

968
01:42:03,614 --> 01:42:07,880
I admit it unusual,
maybe a bit advanced.

969
01:42:07,952 --> 01:42:10,819
Wait a minute.
What's happening?

970
01:42:12,990 --> 01:42:16,983
Well, sir, when we have finished,
you'll go on to the next stage.

971
01:42:17,061 --> 01:42:18,494
I don't mean that!

972
01:42:18,562 --> 01:42:21,793
Ultimately, we'll be called
to face the Creator...

973
01:42:21,866 --> 01:42:24,096
and render up our last account.

974
01:42:24,168 --> 01:42:25,829
It happens to all of us.

975
01:42:25,903 --> 01:42:28,701
That's no answer!
What's happening to me now?

976
01:42:28,772 --> 01:42:30,364
Don't shout! Please!

977
01:42:41,345 --> 01:42:44,007
"Blessed shalt thou be coming in...

978
01:42:44,081 --> 01:42:47,608
and blessed shalt
thou be in going out.

979
01:42:47,685 --> 01:42:50,552
And He said,
'Thou canst not see My face...

980
01:42:51,622 --> 01:42:55,524
for no man can see Me and live."'

981
01:43:08,906 --> 01:43:12,569
"I am the Resurrection and the Life.
He that believeth in Me...

982
01:43:12,643 --> 01:43:16,909
though he were dead,
shall yet he live.

983
01:43:16,980 --> 01:43:21,144
And a stranger shalt thou not oppress,
seeing ye yourselves were strangers."

984
01:43:25,322 --> 01:43:28,052
"He that loveth life shall lose it...

985
01:43:28,125 --> 01:43:33,062
and he that hateth his life in this
world shall keep it unto life eternal.

986
01:43:33,130 --> 01:43:36,531
Fear not thou them
which kill the body."

987
01:43:43,073 --> 01:43:45,041
"I am the door.

988
01:43:45,109 --> 01:43:48,909
By Me, if any man enter in,
shall he be saved."

989
01:44:03,127 --> 01:44:04,719
God be with you, sir.

990
01:44:09,399 --> 01:44:10,991
What's his data?

991
01:44:11,068 --> 01:44:15,596
"Wilson, mesomorph, age 51,
no current diseases.

992
01:44:15,672 --> 01:44:18,163
Requisitioned from
day-room stock May 6.

993
01:44:18,242 --> 01:44:22,542
Released for cadaver use last night.
CPS number 722.

994
01:44:22,613 --> 01:44:26,105
Disposition:
Death by automobile accident...

995
01:44:26,183 --> 01:44:28,515
caused by cerebral hemorrhage."

996
01:44:28,585 --> 01:44:30,519
All right. Acid etch.

997
01:44:30,587 --> 01:44:32,020
Yes, sir.

998
01:44:35,692 --> 01:44:39,093
- What's the solution strength?
- 5% at 10 cc's.

999
01:44:39,163 --> 01:44:40,596
Timer.

1000
01:44:41,532 --> 01:44:42,965
Five minutes.

1001
01:44:51,542 --> 01:44:53,874
You were my best work.

1002
01:44:55,846 --> 01:44:58,076
I'm sorry it all
